<h1 class="subpage-header">About</h1>
<hr/>
<p>
<b>Joint</b> is a JavaScript library that allows you to easily create <b>diagrams</b> and put
them on a web page. The created diagrams are fully interactive. Therefore, the Joint library
is suitable for both implementing a <b>diagramming tool</b> as well as simply publishing your diagrams.
</p>
Main features include:
<ul>
  <li>connecting vector objects with various types of arrows</li>
  <li>interacting with connections (dragging, breaking lines, etc.)</li>
  <li>broken line smoothing</li>
  <li>ready-to-use elements of well-known diagrams (FSA, UML, PN, DEVS)</li>
  <li>building hierarchical diagrams</li>
  <li>serialization (to/from JSON format) <span class="new">NEW in the 0.2 version</span></li>
  <li>extensible - easy implementation of new plugins</li>
  <li>customization - easy customization of arrows and element attributes</li>
</ul>

